{%- comment -%}
  PDP breadcrumb — Home → Collection → Product.

  Why a snippet: every PDP template renders this; centralizing the
  collection-resolution logic here keeps the convention consistent
  and means future tweaks (e.g. a `custom.primary_collection`
  metafield override) only need one edit.

  Resolution order for the middle crumb:
    1. Shopify's `collection` global — populated when the customer
       arrived via `/collections/{handle}/products/{handle}`.
    2. product.collections — first match that isn't Shopify's
       auto-generated `frontpage` (the default "Home page" group
       that effectively every product lands in) or `all` (the
       auto-generated catch-all).
    3. Neither → show just "Home / {product}".

  If a product belongs to no curated collection at all, the middle
  crumb is dropped cleanly. No hardcoded fallback strings.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- liquid
  assign crumb = collection
  if crumb == blank or crumb.handle == 'frontpage' or crumb.handle == 'all'
    assign fallback = nil
    for c in product.collections
      if c.handle == 'frontpage' or c.handle == 'all'
        continue
      endif
      assign fallback = c
      break
    endfor
    if crumb == blank
      assign crumb = fallback
    endif
  endif
-%}
<div class="breadcrumb">
  <a href="{{ routes.root_url }}">Home</a> /
  {%- if crumb -%}
    <a href="{{ crumb.url }}">{{ crumb.title }}</a> /
  {%- endif -%}
  <span>{{ product.title }}</span>
</div>
